GIT COMMANDS:-

 Git clean -n   :-to remove untracked files, which are not added into staging area 

Git merge 1st 
Git checkout master (to come into master branch)
Git revert <commit ID>     to revert the changes we made in commit 
Git tag -a impo -m “impo hai” <commitID>   …..tagging in git
Git tag   ——to see all the tags
Git show <tag>.    ……..to see the commit with out any commit id only with tag 
Git tag -d <tag name>  delete tag
Git clone https://www.github.com/akirepo

Basic Configuration of Git on local machine:-

Git config —global user.name “ski”
Git config —global user.email”aa”      >>>>>for configuration  and to check git config —list


Git add . (To add file to staging area)
Git reset . (n case we mistakenly added any code to staging area so to revert from git add)
Git commit -m “1st commit”  (to commit our code)
Git remote add origin https://github/akirepo.com (to add GitHub repo on local machine)
Git push -u origin master  (to push our code on GitHub)
Git log (to check the history of all commits).
 Git tag -a impo -m “impo hai” <commitID> (to add tag)
Git tag  ( to list all tags)

GIT IGNORE:-
create 1 hidden file .gitignore and enter file format you want to ignore:-
Vi .gitignore
Put format here:- * .css
                               * .java 
:wq

So all the files with .java and .css format will be ignored if we commit any file with these extensions
Git add .gitignore
Git commit -m “ignore”
Git push -u origin master

git branch -D <branch-name>  force deletion
git branch -d <branch-name> to delete any branch 

GIT STASH:-

To put hold on running code and save it to stash, can be pulled back when required.
 
Git stash (to put into stash)
Git stash list 
Git stash apply stash@{0}  (number will be allocated to stash file and this command to bring back file from stash, file will be. Copied not cut and paste )
Git stash clear 





